== scurl: SSL Command Line Downloader ==

To securely download files or webpages from the Internet on the command line, [[Secure_Downloads#Downloads_with_scurl_-_SSL_Command_Line_Downloader|scurl]] is pre-installed in {{project_name}}. scurl should be preferred over wget, since the former enforces strong encryption and is less buggy.

To invoke scurl to download a file, use the following syntax and replace the example URL with the file's location.

{{CodeSelect|code=
scurl --remote-name https://dist.torproject.org/torbrowser/9.5/tor-browser-linux64-9.5_en-US.tar.xz  
}}

This will download <i>tor-browser-linux64-9.5_en-US.tar.xz</i> to the current working directory.

Refer to the [[Secure_Downloads#Downloads_with_scurl_-_SSL_Command_Line_Downloader|scurl]] entry for further examples and a complete description of this tool.

